com.tomtom.speedtools.geometry

Class GeoLine

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tomtom.speedtools.geometry.GeoObject
      • com.tomtom.speedtools.geometry.GeoLine
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JsonRenderable

    @Immutable
public final class GeoLine
extends GeoObject
    Geometric line between two points, from west to east (or, for vertical vectors east=west). If west > east, the vector is wrapped along the long side of Earth. Constructor: GeoLine()

    • Constructor Detail

      • GeoLine

        public GeoLine(@Nonnull
               GeoPoint southWest,
               @Nonnull
               GeoPoint northEast)
        Create a line. A line is always defined from west to east. Note that if the west.longitude > east.longitude that the line is wrapped along the long side of the Earth.
        Parameters:
        southWest - Start point, west side.
        northEast - End point, east side, although east and west may be same longitude.

      • isWrappedOnLongSide

        public boolean isWrappedOnLongSide()
        Return whether the vector is wrapped around the long or short side of Earth. The 'normal case' is that vectors and rectangles are wrapped along the short side indeed.
        Returns:
        True if wrapped around long side, false if wrapped along short side.
